The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Md. Sporting fulfil criteria
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Md. Sporting fulfil criteria
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Mohammedan Sporting officials on Sunday said that the club has been registered as a licensed organisation as per AFC requirements that state that every club playing in the I-League must function as a professional unit.         
	General secretary Sultan Ahmed said: We were looking to get this done for a long time, this will help us get sponsorship deals We registered the club as Mohammedan Sporting Club Pvt. Ltd.         
	Sultan and Jameel Manzar will be looking after the clubs promotional activities. Incidentally, Air India, Mohammedan Sportings opponent in their I-League opener have been granted time to fulfil the same licensing criteria.         
	Ahmed also said that efforts are underway to improve the condition of the club ground. We have already sent a letter to the PWD.                                                                                                                          
